NOTES:
Two-hand tapping exercise in Am pentatonic.

Technique breakdown:
- 5h12 = Hammer from 5 to 12 with left hand
- t = Tap with right hand index or middle finger
- 5h12t5 = Hammer 5-12, tap 5, creates triplet
- p = Pull off

Hand positions:
Left hand:
- Index on 5th fret
- Pinky hammers to 12th fret

Right hand:
- Tap with pick hand index or middle finger
- Tap just behind the fret wire
- Pull away slightly when releasing

Practice steps:
1. Master 5h12 hammer-on first
2. Add tap on same note (5h12t5)
3. Add pull-off (5h12t5h12p5)
4. Increase speed gradually
5. Move to next position (8h15)

Tips:
- Keep tapping finger perpendicular to fretboard
- Tap firmly but don't slam
- All notes should be same volume
- Build speed slowly with metronome

LEGEND:
h = hammer-on
t = tap (right hand)
p = pull-off
l = trill (rapid h/p pattern)
